        "date": "2020-05-13T21:48:38Z",
        "message": "Merge pull request #32 from stepas-toliautas/gcc510-compat\n\nUpdate mspms.h to be compatible with MinGW GCC <= 5.1.0",
        "url": "https://github.com/microsoft/Microsoft-MPI/commit/7ff6bdcdb1d5dc7b791e47457ee2686cd6b3d355"
    },
    {
        "sha": "12244d3b5942dee5e6ffe31431d8b9aee194f45a",
        "author": "Stepas T",
        "email": "stepas.toliautas@ff.vu.lt",
        "date": "2019-12-29T10:24:39Z",
        "message": "Update mspms.h to be compatible with MinGW GCC <= 5.1.0\n\nOn MinGW (TDM) build of 32-bit GCC 5.1.0, which is currently bundled with\nCode::Blocks 17.12 IDE, ws2ipdef.h header is missing, therefore ADDRESS_FAMILY\nand _SOCKADDR_INET types end up not defined in msmps.h. This also affects\nearlier 32-bit GCC versions (tested on TDM 4.9.2). Provided patch introduces\nmissing typedefs when required.\nAdditionally, the following SAL annotations are needed for MinGW GCC <= 5.1.0:\n_Outptr_opt_ (always), _Out_opt_, _In_opt_ (if including mspms.h before mpi.h).\nNOTE: this is backward-compatibility patch, it is not required for newer\nMinGW GCC builds (tested on MinGW-w64 8.1.0, both 32- and 64-bit).",
        "url": "https://github.com/microsoft/Microsoft-MPI/commit/12244d3b5942dee5e6ffe31431d8b9aee194f45a"
    },
